If going back to get that 4th of your quad messed you up so much, why did you do it?<br>
<br>
It seems to me, that if you had continued to kill the remaining three, the druid would have had to deal with the 4th. If he died, the 4th would then come for you. By then you would have finished off the other three. If you didn't, then you still would have had to gate.<br>
